    <fr:title text="Valuation on a frame">Valuation on a frame</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A <html:strong>valuation on a frame</html:strong> is a choice of a set of atomic sentences for each point in the frame, subject to the condition that for all points <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y]]></fr:tex> in the frame, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x R y]]></fr:tex>, then the set assigned to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> must be a subset of the set assigned to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
